      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid properties, pump speed, flow rate) documented with uncertainty bounds and traceable to calibrated instrumentation.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark dataset provides fully documented test conditions with calibrated flow meters (±1.5%) and torque sensors (±0.8%). Morrison lab validation experiments conducted under ISO 17025-accredited conditions. Test conditions adequately characterized."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty U_val) computed and shown to meet acceptance threshold across all assessed operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values were compared against experimental data at five operating points. At four points, agreement is within ±18% of experimental means. However, no formal validation uncertainty U_val was computed; the comparison relied solely on point-estimate percent error without propagating experimental measurement uncertainty into the comparison metric. The absence of a rigorous uncertainty-inclusive comparison metric means the achieved level of output comparison evidence does not satisfy the Gradation 2 requirement, which mandates that validation uncertainty be quantified and incorporated into the pass/fail determination. This gap was identified late in the review cycle; the team judged the qualitative agreement sufficient given the conservative RH < 1 acceptance criterion, but the formal quantitative requirement is not met."
    },
    {
