      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress distribution) are directly relevant to the COU decision quantity (RH index for worst-case hemolysis identification).",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary regulatory QoI for hemolysis assessment and maps directly to the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Shear stress distributions used as secondary QoI to diagnose hemolysis-prone regions. QoI relevance is high and well-justified."
    },
